Today I learnt the basics of the Websites.
I learnt various topics and terminologies:
The Browser: The software which shows the websites and all the contents of the website  
  Web Server: Transfers the contents asked in the requests by the client to the browser  
  DNS Lookup: Converts the required URL request into IP Address    
  HTTP Request: It requests the required content and the website from server and provides it to the client
Web Protocols: Various security and other protocols and features aimed at improving the security of the client and avoiding any malicious attacks. 
  HTTP/HTTPS: HyperText Transfer Protocol - Aims at securing the data and the information of the website and protiecting it from hackers.
  TCP/IP: Internet Protocol. Unique to every website. It secures the website. IP Adresses are the addresses of a particular website which is unique to the website and helps in locating it.
